# TypeScript Style Guide

## Overview

These guidelines build upon our [Core Code Style](../../core/code-style.mdc) with TypeScript-specific patterns and best practices.

## Type System

### Type Annotations

1. Explicit Types:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Explicit types for public APIs
   function processUser(user: User): ProcessedUser {
     return { ...user, lastProcessed: new Date() };
   }

   // ❌ Bad - Relying on inference for public APIs
   function processUser(user) {
     return { ...user, lastProcessed: new Date() };
   }
   ```

2. Type Inference:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Let TypeScript infer obvious types
   const users = ['Alice', 'Bob']; // string[]

   // ❌ Bad - Redundant type annotation
   const users: string[] = ['Alice', 'Bob'];
   ```

### Type Definitions

1. Interfaces vs Types:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Interface for object types
   interface User {
     id: string;
     name: string;
     email: string;
   }

   // ✅ Good - Type for unions/intersections
   type Status = 'active' | 'inactive';
   ```

2. Generic Types:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Descriptive type parameters
   interface Repository<TEntity> {
     findById(id: string): Promise<TEntity>;
   }

   // ❌ Bad - Single-letter type parameters
   interface Repository<T> {
     findById(id: string): Promise<T>;
   }
   ```

## React TypeScript

### Component Types

1. Function Components:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Explicit prop interface
   interface UserCardProps {
     user: User;
     onEdit?: (user: User) => void;
   }

   function UserCard({ user, onEdit }: UserCardProps) {
     return (/* ... */);
   }
   ```

2. Generic Components:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Reusable generic components
   interface ListProps<T> {
     items: T[];
     renderItem: (item: T) => React.ReactNode;
   }

   function List<T>({ items, renderItem }: ListProps<T>) {
     return (/* ... */);
   }
   ```

### Event Handlers

1. Event Types:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Proper event typing
   function handleChange(event: React.ChangeEvent<HTMLInputElement>) {
     const value = event.target.value;
   }

   // ❌ Bad - any type for events
   function handleChange(event: any) {
     const value = event.target.value;
   }
   ```

2. Handler Types:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Explicit handler types
   type SubmitHandler = (data: FormData) => Promise<void>;

   const handleSubmit: SubmitHandler = async (data) => {
     await submitForm(data);
   };
   ```

## State Management

### Type-Safe State

1. Zustand Store:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Type-safe store
   interface AppState {
     user: User | null;
     setUser: (user: User | null) => void;
   }

   const useStore = create<AppState>((set) => ({
     user: null,
     setUser: (user) => set({ user }),
   }));
   ```

2. React Query:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Typed queries
   function useUser(id: string) {
     return useQuery<User, Error>({
       queryKey: ['user', id],
       queryFn: () => fetchUser(id),
     });
   }
   ```

## API Integration

### Type-Safe API Calls

1. Request/Response Types:

   ```typescript
   interface CreateUserRequest {
     name: string;
     email: string;
   }

   interface CreateUserResponse {
     id: string;
     name: string;
     email: string;
     createdAt: string;
   }

   async function createUser(
     data: CreateUserRequest,
   ): Promise<CreateUserResponse> {
     const response = await fetch('/api/users', {
       method: 'POST',
       body: JSON.stringify(data),
     });
     return response.json();
   }
   ```

2. Error Types:

   ```typescript
   interface ApiError {
     code: string;
     message: string;
     details?: Record<string, unknown>;
   }

   async function fetchData<T>(url: string): Promise<T> {
     const response = await fetch(url);
     if (!response.ok) {
       const error: ApiError = await response.json();
       throw new Error(error.message);
     }
     return response.json();
   }
   ```

## Forms

### Type-Safe Forms

1. Form Data Types:

   ```typescript
   interface LoginForm {
     email: string;
     password: string;
     rememberMe: boolean;
   }

   function LoginForm() {
     const form = useForm<LoginForm>({
       defaultValues: {
         email: '',
         password: '',
         rememberMe: false,
       },
     });
   }
   ```

2. Validation Schema:

   ```typescript
   const loginSchema = z.object({
     email: z.string().email(),
     password: z.string().min(8),
     rememberMe: z.boolean(),
   });

   type LoginForm = z.infer<typeof loginSchema>;
   ```

## Testing

### Type-Safe Tests

1. Test Utils:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Typed test utilities
   function renderWithProviders<T>(ui: React.ReactElement, options?: RenderOptions<T>) {
     return render(ui, {
       wrapper: ({ children }) => (
         <Providers>{children}</Providers>
       ),
       ...options,
     });
   }
   ```

2. Mock Types:

   ```typescript
   // ✅ Good - Typed mocks
   const mockUser: User = {
     id: '1',
     name: 'Test User',
     email: 'test@example.com',
   };

   const mockHandleSubmit = vi.fn<[FormData], Promise<void>>();
   ```

